  <title>ACT court fines NRL players' drug supplier</title>
  <content>
A man who supplied cocaine to NRL stars Jesse Bromwich and Kevin Proctor outside a Canberra nightclub has escaped with a fine.
Adrian Mark Crowther on Monday was ordered by the ACT Magistrates Court to pay $4500 for supplying cocaine to the New Zealand internationals on May 6 - the day after the Anzac Test.
He will also be subject to a good behaviour order for 12 months and other fines for possession of cocaine and MDMA.
